## group-id

```yaml
group-id: payment-group
```

Interview Question

> What is Consumer Group?

Think of a consumer group as a **team of workers**.

Example

```
Payment Team

↓

Employee A

Employee B

Employee C
```

All three workers share the workload.

Kafka works exactly the same.

We'll study Consumer Groups in depth later.

For now:

```
Payment Group

↓

Payment Consumer
```

---

## auto-offset-reset

```
earliest
```

Means:

If Kafka doesn't know where this consumer should start...

Begin from the **first message**.

Example

Topic

```
Order1

Order2

Order3
```

Consumer starts today.

With:

```
earliest
```

Consumer reads

```
Order1

Order2

Order3
```

If we used:

```
latest
```

Consumer ignores old messages.

Only future messages are consumed.

