# Common Interview Questions

## 1. Difference between Producer and Consumer?

Producer sends messages.

Consumer reads messages.

---

## 2. What does @KafkaListener do?

It subscribes a Spring method to a Kafka topic and automatically invokes the method when new messages arrive.

---

## 3. Why do we need Deserializers?

Kafka stores bytes.

Consumers must convert those bytes back into Java objects.

---

## 4. Why is auto-offset-reset=earliest useful?

It allows a new consumer (with no committed offsets) to read all existing messages from the beginning of the topic.

